        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2103844890" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12227811627257740761">The style and voice and plot are pure Raymond Chandler, set in a weird future of talking kangaroos and mind-altering drugs. It&apos;s a wild ride that&apos;s largely successful, though not as ambitious as other futuristic genre mash-ups (for example, China Mieville&apos;s The City and The City), in part because it hews pretty closely to a standard Chandler-esque plot and in part because the futuristic elements aren&apos;t quite as developed. Still, there are moments of sheer brilliance here.</span>
  <span id="freeText12227811627257740761" style="display:none">The style and voice and plot are pure Raymond Chandler, set in a weird future of talking kangaroos and mind-altering drugs. It's a wild ride that's largely successful, though not as ambitious as other futuristic genre mash-ups (for example, China Mieville's The City and The City), in part because it hews pretty closely to a standard Chandler-esque plot and in part because the futuristic elements aren't quite as developed. Still, there are moments of sheer brilliance here.</span>
