<span id="freeTextContainer7497585581562273314"><i>“Sometimes it’s better not to think in questions, but I can’t seem to get out of the habit.”</i> <br/>― Jonathan Lethem, Gun, With Occasional Music<br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1525538356i/25486792.jpg' width='400' height='300' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>Science fiction slams into a hard-boiled, noir pulp (imagine &apos;Who Framed Roger Rabbit&apos; written by Chandler and directed by David Lynch&apos;). Fun, quick and in parts even close to brilliant. Lethem is one of those writers I&apos;d stamp with &quot;Most Likely To Disappoint Me&quot;. He has a ton of potential, but far too often I see that potential sizzle away. Most of that ener</span>
  <span id="freeText7497585581562273314" style="display:none"><i>“Sometimes it’s better not to think in questions, but I can’t seem to get out of the habit.”</i> <br>― Jonathan Lethem, Gun, With Occasional Music<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1525538356i/25486792.jpg" width="400" height="300" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>Science fiction slams into a hard-boiled, noir pulp (imagine 'Who Framed Roger Rabbit' written by Chandler and directed by David Lynch'). Fun, quick and in parts even close to brilliant. Lethem is one of those writers I'd stamp with "Most Likely To Disappoint Me". He has a ton of potential, but far too often I see that potential sizzle away. Most of that energy, however, was captured in this book.</span>
